DEFINITIONS

"Stoic Brain Data" means the structured JSON data files in the /stoic-brain/
directory of this repository, including but not limited to: stoic-brain.json,
psychology.json, passions.json, virtue.json, value.json, action.json,
progress.json, and scoring.json, together with any future additions or
modifications to these files.

"SageReasoning API" means the application programming interface hosted at
sagereasoning.com through which the Stoic Brain scoring engine can be accessed.

"Competing Service" means any product, service, API, or system that uses the
Stoic Brain Data to provide reasoning quality evaluation, ethical reasoning
assessment, Stoic-based decision support, reasoning checkpoint wrappers around
existing skills, a marketplace distributing reasoning evaluation skills to
third parties, or an API service that accepts decision-related text input and
returns structured reasoning quality evaluation using Stoic philosophical
mechanisms, whether free or paid, where such service operates independently
of the SageReasoning API.

"Sage Skill Wrappers" means the open-source checkpoint code (SKILL.md files
and invocation logic) that calls SageReasoning API endpoints (sage-guard,
sage-score, sage-iterate) before and after existing skills execute. Wrapper
code is distributed under a permissive open-source licence; the API endpoints
they invoke remain proprietary.

"Original Sage Skills" means proprietary skills developed by SageReasoning
that derive from two or more Stoic Brain mechanisms (Control Filter, Passion
Diagnosis, Appropriate Action, Social Obligation, Iterative Refinement, Value
Assessment). Original Sage Skills are proprietary in their entirety, including
the skill contract (SKILL.md), the server-side implementation, and the
evaluation prompts.

GRANT OF RIGHTS

1. EVALUATION USE. You may read, download, and review the publicly available
   Stoic Brain Data files for the purpose of evaluating whether to integrate
   with the SageReasoning API. This includes testing API integration in
   development environments.

2. API USE. You may use the Stoic Brain Data as provided through the
   SageReasoning API (free or paid tiers) in accordance with the API terms
   of service. Responses received from the API may be stored, displayed, and
   used within your application.

3. ACADEMIC AND PERSONAL STUDY. You may use the Stoic Brain Data for personal
   study, academic research, or educational purposes, provided that any
   publication or public presentation credits SageReasoning as the source.

RESTRICTIONS

4. NO COMPETING SERVICES. You may not use the Stoic Brain Data, in whole or in
   part, to build, train, operate, or offer a Competing Service. This includes
   but is not limited to: incorporating the virtue definitions, scoring weights,
   sub-virtue structures, indifferent rankings, or conflict resolution rules
   into a separate scoring engine.

5. NO REDISTRIBUTION. You may not redistribute, republish, or make available
   the Stoic Brain Data files to third parties, except as embedded within
   responses received from the SageReasoning API.

6. NO DERIVATIVE DATA PRODUCTS. You may not create derivative datasets based
   on the Stoic Brain Data for the purpose of circumventing this licence.

ENTERPRISE LICENCE

7. Organisations requiring self-hosted access to the complete, unredacted Stoic
   Brain Data (including all scoring weights, formulas, and sub-virtue
   structures) may obtain an Enterprise Licence. Contact zeus@sagereasoning.com
   for terms and pricing.

PUBLIC DOMAIN SOURCES

8. This licence covers only SageReasoning's original compilation, structure,
